The course helps to address the problem of acquiring a second language based on an adult language learner. The focus is on the specifics of acquiring Estonian as a second language and the previous research results. The following topics will be addressed:
-	Basic concepts of acquiring a second language, the most important language learning methods
-	Second language acquisition theories
-	The effect of the learner's mother tongue on the acquisition of a second language
-	Research methods for second language acquisition
-	Language errors and error analysis, the written language of the learner
-	The development of language proficiency, CAF-triad (complexity, accuracy, fluency)
-	The role of interaction in the second language acquisition, communication strategies
-	Different levels of success while acquiring a second language, fossilization in the SLA.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to introduce the regularities of adult learner's acquisition of a second language in the context of Estonian as a second language, to give an overview of research on Estonian as a second language, to teach to analyze Estonian language's specifics and development as a second language for the learner.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has completed the course will - know the basic concepts of acquiring a second language; - have an overview of the most important language learning methods and theories of acquiring a second language; - know the methods of researching the acquisition of a second language and is familiar with research on the acquisition of Estonian as a second language; - is aware of the factors that influence the acquisition of a second language; - connect the learned part with the Estonian language and can describe and analyze the Estonian language's specifics and development as a second language.
